parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Poor visibility due to faulty headlights can increase the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
The turn signal system design can cause accidental headlight shut-off, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Easy to turn off headlights while using turn signals

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Incomplete Defects and Lack of Recall Support
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unaddressed defects can lead to safety risks, and lack of support from dealerships or manufacturers can leave owners feeling vulnerable and concerned.
The failure of the driveshaft can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: driveshaft falls out from under the vehicle
sudden loss of power or control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended transmission shifting can cause sudden loss of speed, accidents, or loss of control.
symptoms: Vehicle downshifts to low gear on its own

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ability to shift gears without proper safety measures can cause accidents or injuries, especially if a child is involved.
symptoms: Gear can be shifted without the brake pedal being pressed or the key being in the ignition.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Sensor Sending Unit Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank sensor sending unit can cause inaccurate fuel level readings, leading to unexpected fuel exhaustion, stalling, or difficulty starting the engine, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The malfunction of the sensor associated with the electronic throttle module can cause the vehicle to surge or limp, leading to loss of control, accidents, or engine damage.
The disconnection of the fuel line from the fuel tank can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
